  "diagram_notes": [
    {
      "content": "When Cyera identifies a data resource containing information with sensitive data, this finding surfaced through a Cyera issue which is programmatically communicated to Tines.\nUpon receiving the sensitivity classification from Cyera, Tines automatically applies a corresponding cloud resource tag to the data asset or storage location hosting the identified information. The tag follows a standardized naming convention, such as:\n`Cyera_Sensitivity: <Sensitivity_Level>`\n\nFor example, if Cyera determines that a dataset has Restricted sensitivity classification, Tines will automatically assign the tag: `Cyera_Sensitivity: Restricted`.\nThis process ensures consistent, automated labeling of cloud assets based on data sensitivity, enabling downstream compliance enforcement, access control policies, and audit visibility across the environment.\n\n##  Technical Integration Requirements\n**Cyera**\n- Authentication: Must provide secure authentication details for Tines to connect to Cyera\n\n**Tines**\n- Cloud Provider Integration: Tines must have established, authenticated access (via IAM roles or credentials) to the target cloud environments (e.g., AWS, Azure, GCP) with the necessary permissions to read and write/modify resource tags.\n\n**Cloud Environment (AWS/Azure/GCP)**\n- Tagging Permissions: The IAM role/service principal used by Tines must have the tagging permissions (ec2:CreateTags, s3:PutBucketTagging, etc.) for the specific resource types being monitored (e.g., S3 buckets, RDS instances, Storage Accounts).",
      "position": [
        435,
        195
      ],
      "guid": "c09ac380d8f209e9ea24e42ec5948468",
      "width": 566
    }
  ],
